title: New Images Show Engine Falling Off UPS Plane Before Crashing In Louisville | 10 News
description: Newly released photos have captured the moment an engine tore off a UPS cargo plane before it crashed during takeoff in Louisville in the US.  A preliminary report has revealed there were fatigue cracks in the mount before the aircraft smashed into a storage yard and petroleum recycling factory, killing 14 people. title: White House Defends Trump Telling Female Reporter ‘Quiet Piggy’ | 10 News
description: The White House has defended Donald Trump after he told Bloomberg correspondent Catherine Lucey “quiet piggy” during a press conference onboard Air Force One last week.  White House press secretary Karoline Leavitt said Trump was re-elected because of his bluntness and that members of the media should appreciate his willingness to answer their questions.  “He calls out fake news when he sees it and gets frustrated with reporters who spread false information,” Leavitt said.

title: Trump's Ukraine Peace Plan, Priscilla Presley Interview, Australia-Funded Clinics In Gaza | 10 News+
description: Mohammad Asideh works for Rozana Project, an organisation supported by both Australian government grants and donations from everyday Aussies. He has led a Rozana mission establishing a health clinic in the ruins of the Gaza Strip. During an interview in his brief trip back to Australia, Asideh described the conditions in Gaza. His team recruited local doctors and nurses for the tent clinic, which now provides services to around 2,500 people each month.  Priscilla Presley takes her responsibility to carry on the family legacy incredibly seriously. The actor, author, activist and ex-wife of Elvis is back in Australia for a speaking tour. She sat down with 10 News+ reporter Georgie Tunny and opened up about a whirlwind life shaped by fame, and her search for identity during the years after Elvis.  Kellie Sloane, a former television journalist, has been chosen as the new leader of the New South Wales Liberal Party. She spoke to presenters Hugh Riminton and Ursula Heger on 10 News+ about her vision for the future of the party, touching on all the hot-button issues, including cost of living, net zero, and housing.  Fatima Bosch, Mexico’s contestant at Miss Universe 2025, has been crowned winner at the pageant. This year’s competition made headlines when Bosch led a mass walkout during a pre-pageant meeting, after she was berated and called “dumb” by an event organiser. title: Wieambilla Inquest Finds Killers Had “Delusion Disorder” But Were Not Terrorists | 10 News
description: Two police officers and a neighbour, murdered in Wieambilla in what was, at the time, described as Australia's first Christian terror attack.  But today Queensland's chief coroner says it doesn't meet the definition of 'terror'.  Instead calling the killers “delusional conspiracists” who would rather die  than be captured.
